    "description": "The Honeywell LCD-80 is an 80-character, backlit Liquid Crystal Display (LCD) annunciator designed for use with Honeywell BC200 fire indicator panels (FIP). Up to 32 LCD-80 units can be connected onto a two-wire distributed ring. It operates in two primary modes: \"Terminal\" and \"Annunciator\" mode. Common features include an 80-character backlit LCD (20 characters x 4 lines), time and date display, and the ability to be remotely located up to 1000 metres from the control panel. It features a mutable local piezo sounder with alarm/fault/isolate resound and offers flush or surface mount options. The device utilizes an EIA-485 interface, supporting up to 32 units per FIP. In Terminal mode, the LCD-80 mimics the BC200 display, showing time, date, events, device type identifiers, and alarm/fault/isolate counts, with individual and scroll buttons for events and a mute function for the internal sounder. In Annunciator mode, it functions as a remote alphanumeric display module, showing up to 64 pre-programmed messages (60 characters each) activated by script events in the FIP, with scroll functionality for viewing multiple active messages.",
